metadata.name: Summerland #50
metadata.description:
A random summer mountain landscape based on the technical core of 'Winterland'.
Varies in wind-strength, skycolor, depth and more.
Day/Night cycle based on your local system-time. 
Click/Tap for day/night change.

In Live-Mode...
...press 'r' to toggle responsive/fullscreen mode
...press 's' to save current frame
...click/tap/press space for day/night change

-@TeNinEightNFTs

Created with p5.js using map2.

metadata.name: Microgravity #1107
metadata.description:
Microgravity is part of the fxhash interactive minting experience at The Ever-Evolving World of Art, Art Basel Hong-Kong, 2022.

Scale symmetry of abstract semiliquid forms.

Click on a section of the image to explore deeper.
- Use keys [0-9] to change the detail level.
- Use the "S" key to save a PNG image.
- Use the "R" key to reset the coordinates.

metadata.name: Particularization #5
metadata.description:
“Particularization” is the seventh collection released as a part of NeoMent's "Abandoned Reality" series.

All concepts can be viewed from different levels. You can focus on the details, leaving out the generalized result but understanding the finer points. Or you could emphasize the concept as a whole, comprehending it well overall but missing out on the specifics. It's impossible to choose both, you have to figure out which approach works best for each scenario.

metadata.name: a fleeting moment #175
metadata.description:
Abstract expressionism always has been, and always will be, my first love. With this piece, the initial premise was "can I write a bit of code that will render images in the style that I actually paint in real life?" 

It took several full days of poking and prodding, and I departed from the original mission once I had what I was looking for, but in general, I think I succeeded. My wife was looking over my shoulder at one point, and thought I was looking at a scan of one of my actual paintings, which sounds like success to me. 

Created with love in p5.js
